<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Shipwreck2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Shipwreck,</orth> vb. (O. Edd. <emph>shipwrack</emph>) to throw destructively on rocks or shelves: <cit><quote>their --ed guests,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 115</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed upon a kingdom, where no pity,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 3.1.149" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 1, 149</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ing storms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 2, 26</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>